## Core Artifacts
- `PROJECT_STATE.json` — Stage progression (single source of truth for stages)
- `iteration_log.json` — Experiment history (single source of truth for iterations)
- `project_map.json` — Stable implementation map (single source of truth for durable files and interfaces)
- `docs/20_facts/Codebase_Map.md` — Operator-facing stable codebase map when present
- `docs/_views/` and `docs/_site/` — Generated evidence-preview data and
  human-readable HTML views; Markdown remains the source of truth
- `MEMORY.md` — Human-readable append-only lessons and decisions
- `OPERATOR_CONTEXT.md` — Optional operator preferences, not project facts; write only from explicit operator input
- `.evidence/` — Evidence-chain artifacts for compiled current docs when enabled
- `.auto_iterate/` — Controller-owned runtime state (if auto-iterate is enabled; do not edit manually)

## Context Layers
- Read `.claude/shared/context-layering-policy.md` and `.claude/shared/research-invariants.md` before research planning, documentation, iteration, auto-iteration, or release work.
- Current fact-layer summaries belong in `docs/20_facts/`; they must come from project artifacts or evidence chains.
- `docs/20_facts/Codebase_Map.md` explains stable files, responsibilities, public interfaces, entry points, and maintenance owners.
- Research Conclusion Evidence tables belong in `docs/30_evidence/`; they record sources and candidate norms, not permanent rules.
- `.evidence/**` is tool-owned audit state for Evidence Chains, protocol builds, and review packets; do not hand-edit it.
- Dynamic protocol drafts belong in `docs/35_protocol/`; they are project-local and evidence-derived.
- Human-approved contracts belong in `docs/10_contract/`; they override protocol drafts and operator preferences.
- Current project facts must come from current repo artifacts, logs, configs, metrics, or evidence chains, not from memory alone.

## Language Policy
- `interaction_language`: Match the language of the latest substantive user input unless the user explicitly requests another language.
- `artifact_language`: Use the same language as `interaction_language` for natural-language sections in generated docs and reports unless the user asks otherwise.
- Keep file names, paths, commands, code identifiers, JSON/YAML keys, schema fields, workflow IDs, metric keys, and placeholder tokens in English.
- Treat English wording in templates and examples as structural guidance only; localize headings and narrative text unless a field is explicitly marked English-only.

