## Documentation Evidence and Style Rule
- Before writing docs, read `.claude/shared/documentation-evidence-rule.md` and re-read relevant source artifacts from disk.
- Separate verified facts, inferences, and open questions.
- Use `/protocol-compiler` to compile `docs/30_evidence/**` into reviewable `docs/35_protocol/**` drafts without field profiles.
- For contract, fact, protocol, or release docs, also read `.claude/shared/evidence-chain-rule.md` and compile evidence_chain/source_manifest/doc_audit before replacing current Markdown.
- After durable Markdown docs are finalized, run `/docs-site` to refresh
  `docs/_views/**` and `docs/_site/**`, or report `NOT_RUN`.
- Before implementation, validation, iteration, auto-iteration, or release, read `.claude/shared/contract-gating-rule.md`.
- Use `/protocol-drift-check` when evidence, open questions, negative results, or iteration decisions may have invalidated `docs/35_protocol/**`.
- Use `/review-packet` when the operator needs a short approval/revision/rejection packet for a dynamic-context gate.
- After explicit human approval for a contract, use `tooling/evidence/approve_contract.py` and then re-run the dynamic-context gate.
- Before promoting lessons into `MEMORY.md`, read `.claude/shared/lesson-quality-rule.md`.
- Also read `.claude/shared/documentation-style.md`.
- Keep docs concise and human-readable; prefer ASCII flow diagrams for workflows.
- Before refreshing an existing `docs/*.md`, move the old version into `docs/90_legacy/`.

## Gate Evidence
- Follow the gate ledger format in `.claude/Workflow_Guide.md` when work performs a stage transition, writes current docs, changes stable code, edits canonical state, or prepares WF10/WF11/WF12 readiness.
- Do not treat skill instructions as proof of compliance. Report the actual gate command, result, reason, and artifacts, or state `NOT_RUN` when the gate could not execute.
- Codex approval policy, sandboxing, execpolicy `.rules`, and Codex hooks are runtime guardrails only; Harness gates and human approvals still have to be recorded in project files.

